From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Benjamin Perseghetti <bperseghetti@rudislabs.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] qemu-native: fix setgroups libc syscall emulation

The previous patch missed converting sys_setgroups from _syscall2 to
_libc_syscall2 due to context mismatch in the patch. This causes
apt-get to fail with "setgroups failed - Operation not permitted"
when running under QEMU userspace emulation with QEMU_LIBCSYSCALL=1.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [embedded specific]

Signed-off-by: Benjamin Perseghetti <bperseghetti@rudislabs.com>
---
 linux-user/syscall.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/linux-user/syscall.c b/linux-user/syscall.c
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/linux-user/syscall.c
+++ b/linux-user/syscall.c
@@ -7310,7 +7310,7 @@ static inline int tswapid(int id)
 _libc_syscall1(int, sys_setuid, setuid, uid_t, uid)
 _libc_syscall1(int, sys_setgid, setgid, gid_t, gid)
 _libc_syscall3(int, sys_setresuid, setresuid, uid_t, ruid, uid_t, euid, uid_t, suid)
 _libc_syscall3(int, sys_setresgid, setresgid, gid_t, rgid, gid_t, egid, gid_t, sgid)
-_syscall2(int, sys_setgroups, int, size, gid_t *, grouplist)
+_libc_syscall2(int, sys_setgroups, setgroups, int, size, gid_t *, grouplist)
 _syscall2(int, sys_setreuid, uid_t, ruid, uid_t, euid);
 _syscall2(int, sys_setregid, gid_t, rgid, gid_t, egid);

